# asdf Version Control - Project Runtime Management
#
# Example .tool-versions file for Neovim development environment
#
# This file specifies which runtime versions to use for each language
# asdf will create symlinks in ~/.asdf/shims/<runtime> pointing to these versions
#
# When Neovim (LSPs, formatters) executes commands via these shims:
#   $ ruby -> uses ~/.asdf/shims/ruby -> ruby 3.3.5
#   $ python -> uses ~/.asdf/shims/python -> python 3.12.0
#   $ node -> uses ~/.asdf/shims/node -> node 20.11.0
#   $ rustc -> uses ~/.asdf/shims/rustc/ rust-stable
#
# This ensures CONSISTENT runtime versions across:
# - Neovim LSP servers
# - Formatters (rubocop, ruff, prettier, rustfmt)
# - Terminal commands
#
# Install asdf: https://asdf-vm.com/

ruby 3.3.5
python 3.12.0
nodejs 20.11.0
rust stable
terraform 1.5.7
ruby
# golang 1.23 # Alternative for Ruby if needed
# java openjdk-23 # Alternative for Python if needed